EXPLANATION
BY THE LEGISLATIVE COUNCIL
OF
A N A C T
RELATING TO CRIMINAL PROCEDURE -- ARREST
***
1 This act would prohibit the civil arrest of any person who is attending court either on behalf
2 of themselves or a family or household member. Any person who violates this act would be subject
3 to civil suit, and for contempt of court.
4 This act would take effect upon passage.
